Usage: get_lib_cell_leakage_power [-help] -cell <string> [-file <string>]
                                  [-stateleakagegrp] [ {-view <string> | -delay_corner <string>} [-power_domain <string>]] [ -early  | -late  ]

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
-cell <string>             # Cell Name for which Leakage Power need to be
                           # fetched (string, required)
-delay_corner <string>     # Select cell from specified delay corner
                           # (string, optional)
-early                     # Select cell from early library of the specified
                           # delay corner. If this option is not specified by
                           # default late will be used. (bool, optional)
-file <string>             # Name of the output file. (string, optional)
-late                      # Select cell from late library of the specified
                           # delay corner. If this option is not specified by
                           # default late will be used. (bool, optional)
-power_domain <string>     # Select cell from the library of the specified
                           # power domain (string, optional)
-stateleakagegrp           # Print state dependant leakage power information.
                           # (bool, optional)
-view <string>             # Select the cell from the specified view.
                           # (string, optional)